h3 15. Hosting with Heroku

h5 Sign up & Login
p Sign up with Heroku for one of their free hosting packages.
p Login to your new Heroku account in the browser.

h5 Install Heroku CLI
p Please follow Getting Started on Heroku with Node.js guide at
  code.text-info  #[a( href='https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#set-up' target="_blank" ) https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#set-up]
  span  and install the Heroku Command Line Interface (CLI).

h5 Login to Heroku Server
p In command prompt go to your project directory and type
  code.text-info  heroku login
  span  Then create new Heroku project by typing
  code.text-info  heroku create myProject
p This will create Heroku project and provide you with url.

h5 Deploy your application to Heroku
p In command prompt type
  code.text-info  git push heroku master

h3 Your Project is deployed!
